<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Attaining Spells on Tallon Zek or Vallon Zek</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?srao">srao</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 10:49 a.m. 5/8/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Attaining Spells on Tallon Zek or Vallon Zek<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>This is just an interesting point that I thought I should share. I wanted to start a Half Elf Druid for certain reasons.. But I then realized that in order to get the better spells for a higher lvl druid, you must go to Rivervale or Butcherblock mtns. This makes it useless to be any character that can't get the things they need in their own zone. This would make sense in the other servers, but when you can't get equipment to make your player a reasonably equal threat as that of another race and same class it is tough. Just think as a druid, i can't get better attacking spells unless I am a halfling because in rivervale is where most of the mid-level spells are. But yet, to be high level druid, i need to get spells in Butcherblock, which will pe nearly imposole to get to without teleport, since humans conrtol freeport. So basically being an elf ranger or druid sucks when you get to a higher lvl a need equipment. half eles can't even get patchwork because there are no cats in g faydark. but that is not as big a concern to me as the spells. I think on these 2 servers, they should allow the spells for at least up to lvl20 or 22 to be sold in your home zone. otherwise you will see dominance of classes per race. This needs some serious looking into by the GM's

</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
